                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#163v" facs="164"/>
                    <desc>
                    contains further information about the book.  The two volumes of the Synaxarium were purchased by <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ ማርያም</foreign>, with his own money for two <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወቂት</foreign>. The record also mentions other books he bought. Thereafter, the record (continuing on <locus target="#165r"/>) mentions a list of purchased books owned by the church, 20 books in all, as well other church utensils and priestly garments, crosses. Another record lists books given by other people with a curse on anyone who steals or erases. A final record, written in a different hand, lists more books and materials given to the church
                    </desc>
                    </item>
